The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Dubai, April 22: Talks on the Iran-Pakistan-India gas pipeline are being pursued ?sincerely? and India will not buckle under pressure from any side, including the US, petroleum and natural gas minister Murli Deora said. He is leading a delegation of energy company officials to the three-day 10th International Energy Forum in Doha. The delegation includes IOC chairman Sarthak Behuria, ONGC chairman and managing director Subir Raha and Petronet MD P. Dasgupta.

 Mumbai, April 22: Sun Pharmaceutical Industries today said it has allotted 1.54 lakh equity shares upon conversion of 2,500 foreign currency convertible bonds. The company has allotted the shares at a price of Rs 724.30 apiece upon conversion of 2,500 FCCBs of $1,000 each by bond holders.

 Washington, April 22: The Indian economy continues to be on an accelerated trend with an upsurge in investments, low inflation rate and ample foreign exchange, deputy chairman of the Planning Commission Montek Singh Ahluwalia said.




